modules.description: Represents and formats source code positions with file name, line number, start, and end indices. Provides a pretty-printing function for displaying positions in error messages or logs. Used to track and report precise locations in source files during parsing or analysis tasks.

This module handles source code position tracking and formatting, providing precise location data during parsing or analysis. It includes data types for representing positions with file names, line numbers, and character indices, along with operations to manipulate and compare these positions. A pretty-printing function formats positions for use in error messages or logs. For example, it can report the exact location of a syntax error in a source file, including line and column numbers.
